4. AUTOMATIC LANDING PERFORMANCE. Over 2000 safe and successful automatic landings have been made in all weathers, including fog, in both propeller and jet-engined aircraft without any damage whatsoever to the aircraft. At times the landings have been made at the rate of more than 100 per month without adjustment or alteration to any of the electronic controls. Many of the landings have been photographed and analysed to provide figures on the performance, accuracy and consistency of the system. A wide range of wind conditions have been explored varying from 2 £ knots headwind to 1 o knots tailwind and up to ± 1 £ knots cross-wind component. Also rough air has been experienced on a large number of occasions.

