The principle of operation is illustrated in Fig. n . A narrow beam, high frequency, lock-follow radar located close to the runway in the touch-down region is used to supply continuous information of the position of the aircraft in space (range, elevation, azimuth). This information is passed to a ground computer which compares the measured position with an ideal flight path previously set on the computer and

