More than 12oo fully automatic landings have been made, mostly on a fighter type but supported by a few landings on a wide variety of aircraft, at more than one airfield and in all types of weather. Analysis of some of the flight results indicates a touch-down performance outside the figures quoted for the British system (Section 4), but computer studies have shown where improvements can be made.
The system was developed primarily for the U.S. Navy but it is now being assessed by civil aviation in America. The remarks made in Section

